posters.title: Trigger
posters.label: Action & Adventure
posters.description: As illegal firearms flood into a gun-free South Korea, a resolute cop and a mysterious partner join forces to stop the chaos from sweeping the nation.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: When a shocking mass shooting shatters Korea's calm, Lee Do races to stop the violence — then realizes the threat of illegal guns is just beginning.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: As shootings spread, Lee Do discovers guns in the hands of everyday citizens. When a victim hits close to home, his investigation grows more urgent.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: A police raid uncovers a cache of military weapons. Lee Do and his new ally Moon Baek close in on the arms network as the city reels from bloodshed.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Lee Do confronts a violent standoff and must decide how far to go to stop the killings, while suspicions about Moon Baek threaten their fragile alliance.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Guns reach bullied students and grieving parents, sparking new tragedies. Lee Do uncovers a network delivering weapons to vulnerable people across Korea.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: A gun in the hands of a student spells crisis at school. As panic spreads, Lee Do and Moon Baek race rush to restore order — but it may be too late.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: As fear and confusion grow, police and gangs rush to recover illegal guns. Lee Do feels powerless as the true scale of the arms crisis comes to light.

episodes.title: Episode 8
episodes.description: Police raid the gun syndicate, and rival gangs and old enemies clash in bloody battles. Lee Do is pushed to the limits as violence hits all of Korea.

episodes.title: Episode 9
episodes.description: As guns reach new hands and fear sweeps the nation, Moon Baek's message echoes through the media. Across Korea, people must choose how to respond.

episodes.title: Episode 10
episodes.description: With emotions running high, Lee Do and Moon Baek move toward a crossroads. One final choice will shape Korea's future — or plunge it into darkness.

posters.title: Murderbot
posters.label: Comedy
posters.description: In a high-tech future, a rogue security robot secretly gains free will. To stay hidden, it reluctantly joins a new mission protecting scientists on a dangerous planet...even though it just wants to binge soap operas.

episodes.title: FreeCommerce
episodes.description: On a fresh assignment, Murderbot's newfound free will leads to odd behavior, sparking suspicion from the PreservationAux team.

episodes.title: Eye Contact
episodes.description: Mensah and Bharadwaj risk everything to investigate a mysterious region. Gurathin goes toe-to-toe with Murderbot.

episodes.title: Risk Assessment
episodes.description: The PresAux team heads to a new base to search for answers. Murderbot gets tangled up in a SecUnit showdown.

episodes.title: Escape Velocity Protocol
episodes.description: As an enemy takes aim at Murderbot, an ally tries to orchestrate a getaway. The team grapples with a leadership shake-up and a shocking ultimatum.

episodes.title: Rogue War Tracker Infinite
episodes.description: PresAux pulls out all the stops to forge a path forward. Tensions mount when trust is tested—and a DeltFall survivor joins the fold.

episodes.title: Command Feed
episodes.description: A critical setback sends the team into a spiral. Mensah rolls the dice on a tricky procedure. LeeBeeBee changes her tune.

episodes.title: Complementary Species
episodes.description: Murderbot deals with fallout and detects a critical threat. In hopes of evading danger, the team heads to a new locale full of surprises.

episodes.title: Foreign Object
episodes.description: PresAux receives a dispatch from a rival group. Gurathin taps into Murderbot's bloody past.

episodes.title: All Systems Red
episodes.description: Murderbot calls the shots at a critical rendezvous. Gurathin and Pin-Lee piece together a plan. Mensah makes her own move.

episodes.title: The Perimeter
episodes.description: At the Corporation Rim, PresAux presents a radical request.

posters.title: When Life Gives You Tangerines
posters.label: Drama
posters.description: In Jeju, a spirited girl and a steadfast boy's island story blossoms into a lifelong tale of setbacks and triumphs — proving love endures across time.

episodes.title: Spring in a Heartbeat
episodes.description: Raised by a tenacious mother, a young, bright-eyed Ae-sun has dreams bigger than her village — until an unexpected tragedy changes everything.

episodes.title: Sassy First Love
episodes.description: As love blossoms between Ae-sun and Gwan-sik, they make their first bold move together. But their romantic adventure hits a snag.

episodes.title: Yesterday Was Your Spring
episodes.description: After a dramatic rescue, Ae-sun and Gwan-sik return to Jeju. Soon, Ae-sun resigns herself to a sad fate — leaving Gwan-sik devastated.

episodes.title: The Blazing Summer Sunshine
episodes.description: Summer brings joy as the newlyweds start a life together, but living with Gwan-sik's family tests their happiness — can they find a path to peace?

episodes.title: A Midsummer Night's Full Nets
episodes.description: As Gwan-sik struggles to find work, Ae-sun worries for her family — until a lifeline appears. Soon after, Ae-sun sets her ambitions higher in Jeju.

episodes.title: Life Goes on and On
episodes.description: Just as Ae-sun and Gwan-sik taste the joys of their new life, a summer storm changes everything — testing their will to carry on.

episodes.title: A Fruitful Fall
episodes.description: As the village chief election approaches, Ae-sun faces corrupt opposition. Geum-myeong receives an unusual request that tests her morals.

episodes.title: The Moon Wanes, Yet the Young Heart Remains
episodes.description: When Geum-myeong receives a chance to study in Japan, dreams take flight. Now Ae-sun and Gwan-sik must make a tough decision.

episodes.title: The Wind Goes Whoosh, My Heart Goes Boo-Hoo
episodes.description: Life in a small apartment tests Ae-sun and Gwan-sik as they struggle to parent Yang Eun-myeong. Meanwhile, Geum-myeong juggles love and life in Seoul.

episodes.title: The Storm Sweeps My Heart, the Love Rocks My Heart
episodes.description: While Geum-myeong grows closer to her quirky colleague, Ae-sun's troubling dreams stir real concerns. Do they hold any meaning?

episodes.title: My Love by My Side
episodes.description: As Geum-myeong's engagement moves toward marriage, her heart fills with doubt — will her first love story find its happy ending like her mother's?

episodes.title: A Glistening Winter
episodes.description: Back in Jeju, Geum-myeong mends her heart in familiar surroundings. Ae-sun treasures sweet moments with her loved ones.

episodes.title: Such an Uneven Love
episodes.description: While facing a career setback during an economic downturn, Geum-myeong encounters a familiar face — sparking an unexpected new beginning.

episodes.title: Spread Your Wings and Fly
episodes.description: Ae-sun and Gwan-sik grapple with Yang Eun-myeong's misfortune, sacrificing everything they can to help him. But Eun-myeong's self-confidence takes a hit.

episodes.title: A Spring Every Day
episodes.description: Between new business ventures and career changes, the family faces separate hurdles on their paths — drawing strength from their bond to press ahead.

episodes.title: Here's to All You've Been Through
episodes.description: As the Yang family finally enjoys the fruits of their labor, sudden agony strikes — testing their resolve and the strength of their enduring love.

posters.title: War of the Worlds
posters.label: Science Fiction
posters.description: Will Radford is a top cyber-security analyst for Homeland Security who tracks potential threats to national security through a mass surveillance program, until one day an attack by an unknown entity leads him to question whether the government is hiding something from him... and from the rest of the world.

posters.title: Ice Road: Vengeance
posters.label: Action
posters.description: Big rig ice road driver Mike McCann travels to Nepal to scatter his late brother’s ashes on Mt. Everest. While on a packed tour bus traversing the deadly 12,000 ft. terrain of the infamous Road to the Sky, McCann and his mountain guide encounter a group of mercenaries and must fight to save themselves, the busload of innocent travelers, and the local villagers’ homeland.

posters.title: Karate Kid: Legends
posters.label: Action
posters.description: After a family tragedy, kung fu prodigy Li Fong is uprooted from his home in Beijing and forced to move to New York City with his mother. When a new friend needs his help, Li enters a karate competition – but his skills alone aren't enough. Li's kung fu teacher Mr. Han enlists original Karate Kid Daniel LaRusso for help, and Li learns a new way to fight, merging their two styles into one for the ultimate martial arts showdown.

posters.title: Man with No Past
posters.label: Action
posters.description: Waking up in an unfamiliar city, a man with no memory must confront the mysteries of his own identity. However, his desperate search to uncover the past pits him against a powerful enemy, leading to a showdown that ultimately reveals the truth.

posters.title: The Sandman
posters.label: Sci-Fi & Fantasy
posters.description: After years of imprisonment, Morpheus — the King of Dreams — embarks on a journey across worlds to find what was stolen from him and restore his power.

episodes.title: Sleep of the Just
episodes.description: While searching for an escaped nightmare in the waking world, Morpheus falls prey to Roderick Burgess, an occultist looking to summon and imprison Death.

episodes.title: Imperfect Hosts
episodes.description: Morpheus begins his quest to find his tools of power — his sand, ruby and helm — by paying a visit to a pair of notoriously dysfunctional brothers.

episodes.title: Dream a Little Dream of Me
episodes.description: Morpheus tracks down the last-known person in possession of his sand — and receives an unexpected lesson on humanity. Ethel pays a visit to her son.

episodes.title: A Hope in Hell
episodes.description: A lead on the whereabouts of his helm compels Morpheus to seek an audience with Lucifer. A confused John receives a helping hand from a good Samaritan.
With Morpheus caught off guard, John settles in at a diner to watch the people around him — and put his theory about truth and lies to a terrifying test.

episodes.title: The Sound of Her Wings
episodes.description: Feeling a bit rudderless, Morpheus shadows his hard-working big sister, who offers him advice and encourages him to reconnect with an old acquaintance.

episodes.title: The Doll's House
episodes.description: Lucienne comes to Morpheus with disturbing news. Rose Walker goes in search of family. Admirers of the Corinthian's work scheme to get his attention.

episodes.title: Playing House
episodes.description: As Morpheus closes in on one of his missing creations, Rose ramps up efforts to locate her brother — and unwittingly makes a friend's dream come true.

episodes.title: Collectors
episodes.description: Odd disturbances shake up The Dreaming, Rose sets out on a road trip with a new friend, and The Corinthian arrives with a guest at a creepy convention.

episodes.title: Lost Hearts
episodes.description: As the Dream vortex grows more powerful and the walls between the realms weaken, Rose must make a difficult choice. Morpheus confronts The Corinthian.

episodes.title: Dream of a Thousand Cats/Calliope
episodes.description: In this two-part story collection, a Siamese cat dreaming of a new world and a writer in desperate need of inspiration cross paths with Morpheus.

episodes.title: Season of Mists
episodes.description: When a gathering of the Endless exposes deep-seated grievances, Morpheus embarks on a mission to Hell to free the soul of a condemned mortal.

episodes.title: The Ruler of Hell
episodes.description: Bequeathed the key to Hell, Morpheus throws a lavish banquet to determine which god, demon or faerie can be entrusted with its dark power.

episodes.title: More Devils Than Vast Hell Can Hold
episodes.description: All the world's a stage as Morpheus summons history's greatest dramatist to perform an enchanting play for a supernatural audience.

episodes.title: Brief Lives
episodes.description: Morpheus grudgingly helps Delirium search for their vanished sibling in the waking world — where a deadly force lurks in the shadows.

episodes.title: The Song of Orpheus
episodes.description: To honor a promise to one sibling, Morpheus must shatter a vow to another. In ancient Greece, a wedding-night tragedy turns a son against his father.

episodes.title: Family Blood
episodes.description: Morpheus enlists an expert in the occult to smuggle a deeply personal relic out of Paris — and help him and Delirium find the answers they seek.

episodes.title: Time and Night
episodes.description: With the future of his realm at stake, Morpheus must appeal for help to an authority even greater than the Endless.

episodes.title: Fuel for the Fire
episodes.description: Morpheus recruits a mortal agent for a dangerous mission in the waking world. A change of heart puts a pair of tricksters on a collision course.

episodes.title: The Kindly Ones
episodes.description: Confined to his realm, Morpheus conjures up a new nightmare to do his bidding. The God of Deception deals roughly with an intrusive thorn in his side.

episodes.title: Long Live the King
episodes.description: Fueled by rage, a grieving mother unleashes her wrath upon the Dreaming, as Morpheus confronts the Kindly Ones at the furthest reaches of his kingdom.

episodes.title: A Tale of Graceful Ends
episodes.description: As deities, dreamers and demons unite to mark a momentous occasion, the Endless assemble for a family reunion unlike any other.

episodes.title: A Special Episode - Death: The High Cost of Living
episodes.description: In this standalone episode, a journalist overwhelmed by hopelessness has a life-altering 24 hours after crossing paths with Death on her day off.

posters.title: Revenged Love
posters.label: Drama
posters.description: After Wu Suo-wei's girlfriend dumps him, he decides to get revenge by seducing her new boyfriend, Chi Cheng! It started as a game, but falling in love was never part of the plan.

episodes.title: A Gentleman Will Surely Take Revenge
episodes.description: Wu Suowei starts fresh after heartbreak, but a chance encounter with Chi Cheng leads to unexpected rivalry, mistaken love, and a bold revenge plan.

episodes.title: Ex-Girlfriend's Current Boyfriend
episodes.description: Wu Suowei and Jiang Xiaoshuai plot a clever pursuit, orchestrating chance meetings to draw Chi Cheng in. But as Wu Suowei delves into snake-raising, the hunt takes on a life of its own.

episodes.title: The Apprentice Has Graduated
episodes.description: A fateful park meeting sparks new emotions as Chi Cheng and Wu Suowei hold hands for the first time. Meanwhile, an injury unveils dangerous secrets lurking in the shadows.

episodes.title: He's the One You Like?
episodes.description: Wu Suowei fakes intellect to lure Chi Cheng to a concert, leading to unexpected closeness in the dark and a heartfelt confession with a kiss.

episodes.title: Just Charge Forward, the Bully Has Your Back
episodes.description: Showing concern, Chi Cheng visits Wu Suowei and stays the night. The next day, their flirting continues on the basketball court and Chi Cheng invites him to stay over. At first Wu Suowei refuses, but when Yue Yue shows up, he changes his mind.

episodes.title: My Heart is All Shaken Up
episodes.description: Wu Suowei finds out that all the sugar figurines he’s given to Chi Cheng are kept by him. Chi Cheng wants to develop the relationship further, and Wu Suowei offers a purely physical relationship, to which Chi Cheng responds admitting he still has feelings for his ex-boyfriend.

episodes.title: Anyone Can Be Mad at Me But You
episodes.description: Chi Cheng takes Yue Yue to meet his parents, which ends awkwardly, and Chi Cheng leaves thinking of Wu Suowei. Meanwhile, Wu Suowei finds a batch of rare snakes being sold, and suspects that they originally belonged to Chi Cheng, and decides to investigate.

episodes.title: I Decide Who You're Missing
episodes.description: Wu Suowei tells Ci Cheng that he's planning to start an art installation company. In support, Ci Cheng introduces him to several CEOs who run art-related businesses. Meanwhile, out of jealousy, Weiwei tries to poison Jiltuzheng-but fails. Undeterred, she hires someone to have Jiltuzheng killed...

episodes.title: Snakes Aren't More Important than People
episodes.description: Chi Cheng and Wu Suowei get a tip for a snake-transporting operation, and clash with Guo Chengyu’s men. Wu Suowei gets hurt and his relationship with Chi Cheng develops while hospitalized. Chi Cheng decides to resign and start a business with Wu Suowei, while Yue Yue her secret plot has been discovered.

episodes.title: Can You Turn Straight Again after Being Bent?
episodes.description: Wu Suowei’s company officially launches, and Yue Yue comes by to congratulate him and reconcile, however he rebuffs her and tells her he and Chi Cheng are together. Wu Suowei tries to go back to being straight, but this makes Chi Cheng angry who then asks Jiang Xiaoshuai for help.

episodes.title: Come On, Let’s Go Home and Get Registered
episodes.description: Wu Suo Wei, driven by jealousy, confronts Chi Cheng and reaffirms his possessiveness, demanding exclusivity. The two share intense moments with possessive dialogue and promises of commitment while planning to formalize their relationship.

episodes.title: Why Is He Playing by His Own Rules?
episodes.description: Wu Suo Wei and Chi Cheng's relationship deepens as they officially acknowledge their feelings, marking the start of their committed romance.

episodes.title: Top 10 Best Boyfriend
episodes.description: Wu Suo Wei confesses his reasons for approaching Chi Cheng, and their relationship reaches a new level of sweetness. However, the relationship between Jiang Xiao Shuai and Guo Cheng Yu also changes…

episodes.title: Get Rid of Your Sensitive and Inferior Past
episodes.description: Lunar New Year approaches, and Chi Cheng spends time with Wu Suo Wei and his mother after his own familial obligations. However, Wang Shuo also returns, and an emotional storm is about to reach the happy couple. Meanwhile, Guo Cheng Yu seeks retribution for an injustice done to Jiang Xiao Shuai when he was younger.

posters.description: Once the greatest hitman of all, Taro Sakamoto retired in the name of love. But when his past catches up, he must fight to protect his beloved family.

episodes.description: Sakamoto enjoys a quiet life in retirement with his family. But one day, an old colleague demands he return to the assassin world — or face consequences.

episodes.title: Vs. Son Hee and Bacho
episodes.description: While out on an errand, Sakamoto and Shin encounter Lu Shaotang, the daughter of a mafia boss, who's on the run and targeted by twin assassins.

episodes.title: Welcome to Sugar Park
episodes.description: After learning of the huge bounty on Sakamoto's head, the crew tries to enjoy a family outing at the amusement park while fending off assassins.

episodes.title: Hard-Boiled
episodes.description: With the poison-wielding hitman taken out, the Sakamotos head to their next attraction, where they're ambushed by Dondenkai Ltd's ultimate assassin duo.

episodes.title: Source of Strength
episodes.description: Sakamoto goes all out in a fierce one-on-one duel with Boiled. Meanwhile, ORDER members are tasked with handling a serial case targeting assassins.

episodes.title: Heisuke Mashimo
episodes.description: Hoping to win the million-yen prize, Team Sakamoto enters the shopping district's survival tournament and teams up with a completely clueless sniper.

episodes.title: Jurassic Bastard
episodes.description: While manning the store alone, Lu gets kidnapped by a mysterious group. Sakamoto and Shin pursue her but are halted by an invisible assassin.

episodes.title: Sakamoto's vs. the Lab
episodes.description: To rescue Lu, Sakamoto and Shin infiltrate a top-secret lab seized by assassins. Meanwhile, in the prison cell, Lu meets someone from Shin's childhood.

episodes.title: All Aboard

episodes.title: Bathhouse Roughhouse

episodes.title: Casino Battle
episodes.description: The crew faces Wutang in a high-stakes casino showdown to learn who issued Sakamoto's bounty. Meanwhile, X sends a group of vicious assassins their way

episodes.title: Overload
episodes.description: As Sakamoto gathers intel on the assassins targeting him, ORDER begins hunting the death row inmates. Later, Shin and Lu face a deadly assault.

episodes.title: Just Desserts
episodes.description: Saw's attacks push Shin and Lu to awaken new abilities, turning the tables on the deadly killer. Meanwhile, Dump ambushes Osaragi at a temple.

episodes.title: Strong Assault
episodes.description: The battles rage on even as the crew gets treated by Granny Miya! Minimalist threatens Aoi at the store while Heisuke clashes with Apart at Tokyo Tower.

episodes.title: Round and Round the Tower
episodes.description: Deadly battles with death row inmates break out everywhere! The Minimalist who attacked the Sakamoto Store is defeated by Nagumo of ORDER, disguised as Aoi, leaving only Apart as the only death row inmate remaining.

posters.label: Animation
posters.description: Follow the adventures of brave Wakandan warriors throughout history in this globe-trotting adventure, where they must carry out dangerous missions to retrieve Vibranium artifacts from the enemies of Wakanda. They are the Hatut Zaraze and this is their story.

posters.title: Good Boy
posters.label: Crime
posters.description: After 11 years, the police revive their special recruitment for former national athletes. Once hailed as heroes, these world-class medalists now face harsh realities. Despite financial struggles, unexpected tragedies, and discrimination within the force, the athletes, each with their own story, reunite as a special task force to take on major crimes with the grit and skills they honed as athletes.

episodes.title: Our Twisted Hero
episodes.description: After causing trouble, Dong-ju is demoted to the Insung Metropolitan Police Agency, where he's treated like dead weight and his fellow world-class medalists also face discrimination and scorn. But when a major case erupts, it reignites the fire in their hearts.

episodes.title: Faster, Further, Stronger
episodes.description: At Man-sik's suggestion, a special criminal investigation team is formed with the former world-class medalists. Ready for a fresh start, each member joins with their own hopes and goals, but behind the creation of this special team lurks a hidden agenda.

episodes.title: Million Dollar Baby
episodes.description: Convinced that Ju-yeong is the hit-and-run driver, Dong-ju scrambles to find evidence. Meanwhile, Jong-hyeon heads to the Prosecutors' Office at Man-sik's request to investigate Gyeong-il's case, and Ju-yeong meets someone in the shadows.

episodes.title: Float Like a Butterfly
episodes.description: The Special Criminal Investigation Team is now complete with Han-na's return and Jong-hyeon joining. They launch a full-scale investigation into Gyeong-il's death and Min Ju-yeong. As they split into teams and close in on their targets, Han-na receives her father's case files.

episodes.title: Punch-Drunk Love
episodes.description: While investigating Ju-yeong, the Special Criminal Investigation Team is forced to hand him over to the prosecution after their sudden intervention. Dong-ju is hospitalized for tests following his car accident, and the team digs deeper into Ju-yeong's true identity and his connections to the prosecution.

episodes.title: Counterpunch
episodes.description: Using Han-na's surprise kiss as an excuse, Dong-ju heads out alone with her on an investigation and discovers Ju-yeong's burner phone. Jong-hyeon finds himself growing uneasy as Dong-ju and Han-na get closer. Meanwhile, Drugmon, under surveillance in an apartment, begins plotting her escape.

episodes.title: Par Terre Par Terre
episodes.description: Dong-ju's assault puts the Special Criminal Investigation Team in a major crisis. Man-sik fights to keep the team together, while the others continue investigating Ju-yeong, weighed down by uncertainty. Meanwhile, Ju-yeong leaves the hospital and heads to an unknown destination.

episodes.title: The Aimless Bullet
episodes.description: The Special Criminal Investigation Team catches wind of Ju-yeong's drug smuggling and infiltrates the customs office disguised as a quarantine unit. Following a lead left by Drugmon, they manage to find the container hiding the drugs but walk straight into a trap set by Ju-yeong.

episodes.title: Allez
episodes.description: Han-na is kidnapped, and Dong-ju and Jong-hyeon rush to rescue her, only to find themselves trapped in a deadly crisis. Just when it seems there's no way out, an unexpected gunshot rings out. With an unforeseen sacrifice shaking the team, will they survive?

episodes.title: Time-out
episodes.description: The Special Criminal Investigation Team is disbanded in the end. Dong-ju quietly prepares revenge against Ju-yeong alone, but his reckless move only invites a greater crisis. Catching on to his plan, Ju-yeong launches a counterstrike.

episodes.title: Countdown
episodes.description: The Special Criminal Investigation Team reunites and uncovers Joo-young's big secret. Frightened by Dong-joo's countdown challenge, Joo-young takes desperate measures. So who will win in the end?

episodes.title: Foul
episodes.description: Falling into Ju-yeong's trap, Dong-ju suffers a critical injury and faces his greatest crisis yet. Will he push through or fall where he stands?

episodes.title: Load, Start...Don't Stop
episodes.description: With no way to retreat, Dong-joo and the team launch their final all-out attack on Joo-young. Moving in without hesitation, they soon face a fierce counterattack and unexpected difficulties. What is written in their fate?

episodes.title: Kings Never Die
episodes.description: No description available

episodes.title: On the Ropes
episodes.description: The entire Inseong police force unites and launches a massive operation against Joo-young's gang. But just when they are close to victory, Joo-young's most devastating counterattack throws the entire city into chaos.

episodes.title: We Are The Champions
episodes.description: Amidst the chaos, Dong-joo and Team Inseong begin their decisive battle to determine the fate of the city. Carrying the weight of everyone's hopes and expectations on their backs, will they be able to achieve the ultimate victory and emerge as true heroes?

To survive, he must wield a new power and join the rogue Cleaners. Rudo doesn’t just aim to battle monsters, but the corrupt who cast him into Hell.

episodes.title: The Sphere
episodes.description: Bullied outcast Rudo finds respite in repurposing trash, until a terrible tragedy changes his life forever.

episodes.title: The Inhabited

episodes.title: The Ground

Ludo, who has also awakened to his power as a Giver, is scouted by Enjin to join an organization called the Cleaners, which fights against the Spotted Beasts born from garbage. Ludo accepts the offer in order to find a way to return to the Heavenly World where he has lived until now, but he suddenly gets into a fight with his trainer, Zanca.

posters.description: As illegal firearms flood into a gun-free South Korea, a resolute cop and a mysterious partner join forces to stop the chaos from sweeping the nation.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: When a shocking mass shooting shatters Korea's calm, Lee Do races to stop the violence — then realizes the threat of illegal guns is just beginning.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: As shootings spread, Lee Do discovers guns in the hands of everyday citizens. When a victim hits close to home, his investigation grows more urgent.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: A police raid uncovers a cache of military weapons. Lee Do and his new ally Moon Baek close in on the arms network as the city reels from bloodshed.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Lee Do confronts a violent standoff and must decide how far to go to stop the killings, while suspicions about Moon Baek threaten their fragile alliance.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Guns reach bullied students and grieving parents, sparking new tragedies. Lee Do uncovers a network delivering weapons to vulnerable people across Korea.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: A gun in the hands of a student spells crisis at school. As panic spreads, Lee Do and Moon Baek race rush to restore order — but it may be too late.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: As fear and confusion grow, police and gangs rush to recover illegal guns. Lee Do feels powerless as the true scale of the arms crisis comes to light.

episodes.title: Episode 8
episodes.description: Police raid the gun syndicate, and rival gangs and old enemies clash in bloody battles. Lee Do is pushed to the limits as violence hits all of Korea.

episodes.title: Episode 9
episodes.description: As guns reach new hands and fear sweeps the nation, Moon Baek's message echoes through the media. Across Korea, people must choose how to respond.

episodes.title: Episode 10
episodes.description: With emotions running high, Lee Do and Moon Baek move toward a crossroads. One final choice will shape Korea's future — or plunge it into darkness.

posters.description: Miniseries that follow the life and career of Mexican actor, comedian and producer Roberto Gómez Bolaños, known for being the creator of El Chavo del 8, El Chapulín Colorado and Chespirito.

episodes.title: Cobbler, Stick to Thy Last
episodes.description: In 1951, Roberto pursues his dream of a career in television, defying his mother's orders, to try his hand at both comedy...and love.

episodes.title: Every Cloud Has a Silver Lining
episodes.description: Now known as Chespirito, Roberto decides to try his luck on another channel and, despite some setbacks, manages to put together a successful sketch.

episodes.title: Don't Get 'Reathers Fluffled!
episodes.description: Doctor Chapatín's resignation puts Roberto's career at risk, so he must create a new character before the executives give his place to another comedian. But it's his cunning and an old idea that will save the day.

episodes.title: It's Just That You Have No Patience for Me
episodes.description: In 1936, a young Roberto is sent to Guadalajara, where he struggles to fit in. Decades later, the now seasoned Chespirito finds himself lost without his biggest supporters at Channel 8, but memories of childhood help the comic conceive El Chavo del Ocho -- his most successful series yet.

episodes.title: He Who Laughs Last…
episodes.description: As El Chavo gains popularity and Roberto is given more creative freedom, Channel 8's competitors vie to bring Chespirito on board. Meanwhile, success and fame cause trouble for Roberto, his team and his family, leading to the comic's most prolific -- and devastating -- era.

episodes.title: The Price of Fame
episodes.description: With Roberto's career on the rise, the cast of El Chavo embarks on an international tour. But while her husband dives headfirst into his work, Graciela struggles with her new reality as the wife of a star.

episodes.title: On the Fence
episodes.description: As Chespirito's characters reach the height of their popularity across Latin America, Roberto relishes in his newfound level of fame -- while growing more distant from his family back home. In Acapulco, Roberto finds himself struggling with what he feels and what he thinks is right.

episodes.title: It Was Worth It
episodes.description: Roberto gets his team together for one last project -- a comedic soccer film called El Chanfle. While the cast and crew come to blows on set, Roberto faces a choice between his past and his future. Later, a warm welcome in Colombia reminds Chespirito of his true purpose: making people laugh.

episodes.title: Million Dollar Baby

episodes.title: Float Like a Butterfly

They launch a full-scale investigation into Gyeong-il's death and Min Ju-yeong. As they split into teams and close in on their targets, Han-na receives her father's case files.

episodes.title: Punch-Drunk Love

Dong-ju is hospitalized for tests following his car accident, and the team digs deeper into Ju-yeong's true identity and his connections to the prosecution.

episodes.title: Counterpunch
episodes.description: Using Han-na's surprise kiss as an excuse, Dong-ju heads out alone with her on an investigation and discovers Ju-yeong's burner phone. Jong-hyeon finds himself growing uneasy as Dong-ju and Han-na get closer. Meanwhile, Drugmon, under surveillance in an apartment, begins plotting her escape.

episodes.title: Par Terre Par Terre
episodes.description: Dong-ju's assault puts the Special Criminal Investigation Team in a major crisis. Man-sik fights to keep the team together, while the others continue investigating Ju-yeong, weighed down by uncertainty. Meanwhile, Ju-yeong leaves the hospital and heads to an unknown destination.

episodes.title: The Aimless Bullet
episodes.description: The Special Criminal Investigation Team catches wind of Ju-yeong's drug smuggling and infiltrates the customs office disguised as a quarantine unit. Following a lead left by Drugmon, they manage to find the container hiding the drugs but walk straight into a trap set by Ju-yeong.

episodes.title: Allez
episodes.description: Han-na is kidnapped, and Dong-ju and Jong-hyeon rush to rescue her, only to find themselves trapped in a deadly crisis. Just when it seems there's no way out, an unexpected gunshot rings out. With an unforeseen sacrifice shaking the team, will they survive?

episodes.title: Time-out
episodes.description: The Special Criminal Investigation Team is disbanded in the end. Dong-ju quietly prepares revenge against Ju-yeong alone, but his reckless move only invites a greater crisis. Catching on to his plan, Ju-yeong launches a counterstrike.

episodes.title: Countdown
episodes.description: The Special Criminal Investigation Team reunites and uncovers Joo-young's big secret. Frightened by Dong-joo's countdown challenge, Joo-young takes desperate measures. So who will win in the end?

episodes.title: Foul
episodes.description: Falling into Ju-yeong's trap, Dong-ju suffers a critical injury and faces his greatest crisis yet. Will he push through or fall where he stands?

episodes.title: Load, Start...Don't Stop
episodes.description: With no way to retreat, Dong-joo and the team launch their final all-out attack on Joo-young. Moving in without hesitation, they soon face a fierce counterattack and unexpected difficulties. What is written in their fate?

episodes.title: Kings Never Die
episodes.description: No description available

episodes.title: On the Ropes
episodes.description: The entire Inseong police force unites and launches a massive operation against Joo-young's gang. But just when they are close to victory, Joo-young's most devastating counterattack throws the entire city into chaos.

episodes.title: We Are The Champions
